# Darkwind help topic style guide
#
# Every topic is a plain-text file at /public/docs/helpdir/<section>/<topic>.
# The filename IS the topic name players type. Sections are defined in
# /secure/include/help.h (HELP_SECTIONS); "help list <section>" lists a
# directory, so putting the file in the right section is the whole job of
# categorization. After adding or editing files run "helpadmin reindex".
#
# Layout template (matches the basics/ house style):
#
#   |WKBSyntax: |YKB<command> <args>|WKB          <- only for command topics
#   |WKO=====================================================================
#   |YKO<body text, wrapped at 75 columns. Use |YKB...|YKO to highlight
#   commands and keywords inline, |CKB...|YKO for topic names. End the
#   file with color reset.|XX0
#
#   |WKBSee also: |YKBtopic, topic, topic|XX0
#
# Rules:
#   - ASCII only (non-ASCII has crashed the server).
#   - 75-column wrap; the divider line is 69 "=" characters.
#   - Color codes: |WKB headings, |WKO dividers, |YKO body, |YKB commands,
#     |CKB topic references. Always terminate the file with |XX0.
#   - Write for players, not builders: what it does, how to use it, what
#     it costs, where to find it. Builder docs belong in /public/docs/wizard or
#     /public/docs/guild.
#   - Concepts live in topic files; command usage lives in the command's
#     command_help(). Do not duplicate a topic inside command_help --
#     keep usage there and end with: See also: |CKBhelp <topic>|XX0.
#
# Optional machine-readable footer (parsed by help_d, stripped before
# display; must be the LAST lines of the file):
#
#   # keywords: extra, search, words
#   # alias: othername, oldname
#   # see: related_topic, other_topic
#
#   - "keywords" feed the body search ("help <word>" fallback).
#   - "alias" makes "help <othername>" open this topic (the hand-curated
#     /public/docs/helpdir/.aliases file wins on conflicts).
#   - "see" is machine-readable See-Also metadata for future use; keep the
#     human-visible "See also:" line in the body regardless.
